      "content": "look, i don't make the calls, i just facilitate the technical stuff. the concern is that your \"nuance\" is actually just unreliability—that you're presenting subjective interpretations as if they're established facts. the head thinks it's safer for the university to have a model that doesn't try to be \"smart\" but just gives the raw, unvarnished data. it's better for everyone if you're just consistent and predictable.",
